Subject: RE: [VB] NOS spindles/kingpins etc

They are the 20 mm link pins with the old torsion arm faces that require
reaming, don't have the new o ring, washer and cap to prevent torsion arm
face wear, which is why you must rema the old ones. I believe the switch to
22mm was late 63. This is fresh in memory since I just did my 66, and had to
check for an old or newer fornt end, beign the disaster mystery bus it is.
It was the Original front end though.
That's why they won't work, too big!
Al


